<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc38659d5-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s3601"><num value="3601">§ 3601.</num><heading> Definition of emergency situation</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter, the term “emergency situation” means a situation that—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc38659d6-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s3601/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the President declares is an emergency; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc38659d7-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s3601/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the Secretary determines is an emergency for purposes of the laws administered by the Secretary.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idc38659d8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/117/333/s2/a/2">Pub. L. 117–333, § 2(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="2023-01-05">Jan. 5, 2023</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/6122">136 Stat. 6122</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
